item.title: Changing the "Teleports" Names
item.dc:creator: @Kozs Kozs
item.description:
@Kozs wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:12, topic:536589”][quote author=Kozs link=topic=655402.msg4388844#msg4388844 date=1386716410]

sendFrame126 should do you wonders.
I believe the ID of that text is 1382.

How would I figure that part out?

1382 is the “Pking teleport” part… Not the Camelot part

My bad. I was off by a number. 1383 is the cammy text.
And figure what out? sendframe126? for pi it’s c.getPA().sendFrame126(“Your text”, 1383);
It’s the same thing you used for the pking text, but with a different number.

How did you find the numbers…

	sendFrame126("Pking Teleport", 1383); worked but what about the top corner?

[/quote]
No idea for the id of the top corner. And to answer where I got the ID’s, I have a dump of basically all the standard 317’s text ID’s. The ID for the top corner may possibly be 1380-1390. But I’m not sure.[/quote]

Link?
